Security Audit Phases
Phase	Purpose	Key Activities	Deliverables
1. Planning & Preparation	Define the audit scope and objectives.	Determine systems to audit, identify risks, gather documentation, assign team members, establish timeline.	Audit Plan, Scope Document
2. Information Gathering	Understand the environment being audited.	Review policies, interview personnel, inventory assets, review architecture diagrams, identify applicable regulations.	Asset Inventory, Documentation Review
3. Risk Assessment	Identify the organization's highest risks.	Evaluate threats, vulnerabilities, likelihood, impact, and existing controls.	Risk Assessment Report
4. Control Evaluation	Determine whether security controls are effective.	Review administrative, technical, and physical controls against standards like NIST, ISO 27001, and CIS Controls.	Control Assessment
5. Testing & Validation	Verify controls actually work.	Vulnerability scanning, configuration reviews, access reviews, log analysis, penetration testing (if authorized).	Test Results, Evidence
6. Findings & Analysis	Analyze weaknesses discovered during testing.	Prioritize findings by severity, determine root causes, evaluate business impact.	Findings Report
7. Reporting	Communicate results to management.	Write executive summary, technical findings, recommendations, risk ratings, compliance status.	Final Audit Report
8. Remediation	Fix identified security issues.	Apply patches, improve policies, update configurations, implement new controls.	Remediation Plan
9. Follow-Up Audit	Verify corrective actions were completed.	Re-test vulnerabilities, confirm controls are effective, close findings.	Follow-Up Report
